The paper focuses on visual question answering, which involves both computer vision and natural language processing. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper proposes a novel method for feature fusion, which involves machine learning techniques such as attention mechanisms and dynamic information flow, indicating that it could also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories.
